Product Requirements Document (PRD)
Project Name: "A Message Someone Left For You" (Internal Codename: Project Delulu)
Document Version: 1.0
Target Platforms: Web Browser (Mobile-First Optimization, Desktop Compatible)
Expected Session Length: 30–60 seconds

1. Product Overview
1.1 Vision
To create a short, viral, interactive web experience that bait-and-switches the user. It begins as an intimate, wholesome, and romantic interactive message, building emotional anticipation, before abruptly shattering the illusion with a loud, chaotic, meme-style reality check.

1.2 Core Objectives

High Completion Rate: Keep interactions simple and engaging to ensure users reach the punchline.

Viral Loop Generation: Elicit a strong enough reaction (laughter/surprise) that the user immediately wants to trick their friends using the built-in share mechanics.

2. User Flow & Screen Requirements
Phase 1: The Hook (Screens 1 & 2)
State 1: The Landing Page

UI Elements: Soft pastel pink background, floating CSS sparkles, centered illustrated wax-sealed envelope. Text: "Someone who cares about you left a message." Subtext: "Open the envelope to read it."

Interaction: User clicks/taps the envelope. (Crucial: This initial click serves as the DOM interaction required by modern browsers to allow autoplaying audio for the rest of the experience).

Audio/Animation Trigger: Soft piano music begins. Paper rustling sound plays. Envelope opening animation triggers.

State 2: The Letter Unfolding

UI Elements: A digital letter that unfolds downward in 4 distinct sections. Uses an elegant, handwritten cursive font.

Interaction: User clicks to unfold each section.

Progression:

Fold 1: "You have a way of making people smile." (Trigger: Soft sparkle animation).

Fold 2: "Your energy makes the world feel lighter." (Trigger: Music stems increase/become more emotional).

Fold 3: "Someone really appreciates having you in their life." (Trigger: Floating CSS hearts).

Fold 4: "And they wanted you to know something important..." * Exit: A "Continue" button fades in. Clicking initiates Phase 2.

Phase 2: The Build-Up (Screens 3 & 4)
State 3: The Jar of Stars

Transition: Letter fades out, background cross-fades from pastel pink to a dark, calming night sky.

UI Elements: A glass jar filled with 6 glowing stars. Text: "Each star contains something someone wanted to tell you. Click the jar to open them."

Audio: Piano fades into soft, ambient night-time music/chords.

State 4: Star Extraction

Interaction: User clicks the jar 6 times.

Animation/Audio: Each click plays a delicate chime. A star floats upward and expands into a text bubble.

Sequence:

"You matter more than you think."

"You make someone's day brighter."

"Your presence is appreciated."

"You're stronger than you realize."

"Someone notices the little things you do."

"And they wanted you to know..."

Exit: A "Reveal who it is" button appears.

Phase 3: The Fake-Out & The Drop (Screens 5 & 6)
State 5: The Fake Suspense (Loading)

UI Elements: Screen darkens. A faux terminal/loading bar appears.

Text sequence: "Analyzing..." -> "Scanning messages..." -> "Checking memories..."

Timing: Lasts exactly 3-4 seconds to build maximum anticipation.

State 6: The Ragebait Twist (The Drop)

Audio Trigger: CRITICAL MOMENT. Ambient music abruptly cuts off with a loud record scratch.

Visual Trigger: Screen shakes violently (CSS keyframe animation). Background instantly flips to a harsh, contrasting color or dark grey.

UI Sequence (Cascading with sound effects):

Vine Boom Sound: Bold meme font appears: "BRO STOP DAYDREAMING 💀"

Discord Notification Sound: Text appears: "YOU CLICKED A RANDOM WEBSITE"

Loud "FAHHH" Sound/Error sound: Text appears: "NOBODY CONFESSED ANYTHING"

Phase 4: The Aftermath (Screens 7 & 8)
State 7: The Reality Check

UI Elements: Playful, chaotic UI.

Text: "THIS IS WHY YOU'RE DELULU" followed by a cascading list: "GO DRINK WATER", "FINISH YOUR WORK", "AND TOUCH GRASS".

State 8: The Viral Loop (Call to Action)

UI Elements: Two buttons appear.

Primary Action: "Send this to someone who daydreams too much" (Triggers native Web Share API on mobile, or copies URL to clipboard on desktop).

Secondary Action: "Try again (maybe someone will confess this time)" (Refreshes the state back to Screen 1).

3. Asset Requirements
3.1 Audio (MP3/OGG)

Wholesome: Soft piano track, ambient night track, paper rustle, unfolding paper flap (x4), soft UI chime.

Meme: Record scratch, Vine boom, Discord ping, Windows error "bonk", generic "FAHHH" sound.

3.2 Visuals (SVG/WebP)

Wax-sealed envelope (closed and open states).

Folded letter segments.

Glass jar (transparent PNG/SVG).

Glowing stars.

3.3 Typography

Wholesome Phase: A high-quality Google Font cursive (e.g., Dancing Script, Caveat, or Great Vibes).

Meme Phase: Impact, Arial Black, or standard system bold fonts (all caps).

4. Technical & Non-Functional Requirements
Mobile-First: 80%+ of users will likely open this via a text or DM link. The UI must be perfectly centered and responsive on vertical viewports.

Audio Policy Handling: Browsers block autoplaying audio. The "Click to open envelope" interaction acts as the mandatory user gesture to unlock the Web Audio API context for the rest of the flow.

Performance: All assets (especially audio) must be preloaded in the background during Screen 1 so the "Twist" happens instantly with zero buffering delay.